# API Development Patterns

## HTTP Framework
- Use Gin framework for REST API endpoints
- Follow RESTful design principles
- Implement proper HTTP status codes
- Use middleware for cross-cutting concerns

## Request/Response Handling
- Validate input data using struct tags
- Return consistent JSON response formats
- Handle errors gracefully with proper HTTP status codes
- Implement request logging and monitoring

## Authentication & Security
- Implement proper authentication mechanisms
- Use HTTPS in production
- Validate and sanitize all inputs
- Implement rate limiting for API endpoints

## Error Handling
- Return structured error responses
- Log errors with appropriate context
- Use consistent error message formats
- Implement proper error codes

## Documentation
- Document API endpoints with comments
- Use OpenAPI/Swagger when possible
- Provide example requests and responses
- Keep API documentation up to date

## Testing
- Write integration tests for API endpoints
- Mock external dependencies
- Test error scenarios and edge cases
- Use test utilities for common operations
